"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkbuildbuddy_docs_website=globalThis.webpackChunkbuildbuddy_docs_website||[]).push([[1200],{27625(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/bazel-remote-cache-cdc","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/bazel-remote-cache-cdc","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/bazel-remote-cache-cdc.md","source":"@site/changelog/bazel-remote-cache-cdc.md","title":"End-to-end CDC support","description":"We\'re excited to announce end-to-end content-defined chunking (CDC) support for Bazel remote caching in BuildBuddy.","date":"2026-04-23T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"bazel","permalink":"/changelog/tags/bazel"},{"inline":true,"label":"featured","permalink":"/changelog/tags/featured"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Tyler French","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tylerdfrench/","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/66684063?v=4","key":"tyler-french","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"End-to-end CDC support","date":"2026-04-23T10:00:00.000Z","authors":"tyler-french","tags":["bazel","featured"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Run log streaming","permalink":"/changelog/cli-run-log-streaming"}},"content":"We\'re excited to announce end-to-end content-defined chunking (CDC) support for Bazel remote caching in BuildBuddy.\\n\\nWith Bazel 9.1\'s new `--experimental_remote_cache_chunking` support, large outputs like linker artifacts can be uploaded and downloaded in content-defined chunks instead of as monolithic blobs. That lets BuildBuddy deduplicate similar artifacts across builds, reducing upload bandwidth and storage usage. In one benchmark on the BuildBuddy repo, this showed roughly 40% less uploaded data and a roughly 40% smaller disk cache. Breaking large blobs into smaller reusable pieces also means fewer long-running RPCs and more granular retries.\\n\\nTo enable it, add these flags to your `.bazelrc`:\\n\\n```text\\ncommon --experimental_remote_cache_chunking\\ncommon --remote_header=x-buildbuddy-cdc-enabled=true\\n```\\n\\nTo see the download-side savings, you should also set `--disk_cache`, since the downloaded chunks need to be stored somewhere in order to be reused locally. We also recommend setting <code className=\\"flag\\">--experimental_disk_cache_gc_max_age</code> to a value below your remote cache TTL\u2014for example, `3h`, or `1d` if your remote TTL is longer.\\n\\nBazel 9.1 is required today, and this support will also be backported to Bazel 8.7.\\n\\nFor more background, see [bazelbuild/bazel#28437](https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/28437).\\n\\nWe\'ll share a longer blog post soon with more details on the technical journey behind this work."},{"id":"/cli-run-log-streaming","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/cli-run-log-streaming","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/cli-run-log-streaming.md","source":"@site/changelog/cli-run-log-streaming.md","title":"Run log streaming","description":"In addition to build logs, you can now use the bb CLI to stream bazel run executable output to our servers and view live-updating run logs from the UI.","date":"2026-04-21T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"bazel","permalink":"/changelog/tags/bazel"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Maggie Lou","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/maggie-lou-4a3bb110a/","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13951661","key":"maggie","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Run log streaming","date":"2026-04-21T10:00:00.000Z","authors":"maggie","tags":["bazel"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"End-to-end CDC support","permalink":"/changelog/bazel-remote-cache-cdc"},"nextItem":{"title":"BuildBuddy MCP server","permalink":"/changelog/buildbuddy-mcp-server"}},"content":"In addition to build logs, you can now use the [`bb` CLI](https://buildbuddy.io/cli) to stream `bazel run` executable output to our servers and view live-updating run logs from the UI.\\n\\n![run log streaming](../static/img/changelog/run-log-streaming.webp)\\n\\nThis gives you a durable record of executable output, making it easy to share logs with teammates, or letting you monitor runs while away from your terminal.\\n\\nTo use it:\\n\\n```bash\\nbb run //app:server --stream_run_logs\\n```\\n\\nBy default, if streaming fails, the executable will continue to run. To fail the command immediately, use `--on_stream_run_logs_failure=fail`."},{"id":"/buildbuddy-mcp-server","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/buildbuddy-mcp-server","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/buildbuddy-mcp-server.md","source":"@site/changelog/buildbuddy-mcp-server.md","title":"BuildBuddy MCP server","description":"BuildBuddy now exposes an MCP endpoint for coding agents and other","date":"2026-04-15T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"AI","permalink":"/changelog/tags/ai"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Brandon Duffany","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/brandon-duffany-39b7217a","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2414826?v=4","key":"brandon","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"BuildBuddy MCP server","date":"2026-04-15T10:00:00.000Z","authors":"brandon","tags":["AI"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Run log streaming","permalink":"/changelog/cli-run-log-streaming"},"nextItem":{"title":"Improved handling of short-lived secrets in remote execution","permalink":"/changelog/secret-env-overrides"}},"content":"BuildBuddy now exposes an MCP endpoint for coding agents and other\\nMCP-capable clients.\\n\\nMCP provides a way to let agents explore BuildBuddy data for mostly\\nread-only workflows like build and test metadata, logs, artifacts, target\\nstatuses, and more.\\n\\nYou can connect agents like Codex, Claude Code, and Gemini CLI to:\\n\\n```text\\nhttps://YOUR-BUILDBUDDY-ORGANIZATION.buildbuddy.io/mcp\\n```\\n\\nAuthenticate with:\\n\\n```text\\nAuthorization: Bearer <api-key>\\n```\\n\\nSee the new\\n[BuildBuddy MCP Server docs](https://www.buildbuddy.io/docs/enterprise-mcp)\\nfor setup instructions and configuration examples."},{"id":"/secret-env-overrides","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/secret-env-overrides","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/secret-env-overrides.md","source":"@site/changelog/secret-env-overrides.md","title":"Improved handling of short-lived secrets in remote execution","description":"BuildBuddy has supported passing short-lived secrets to remote actions via the env-overrides platform property, which redacts values from action cache entries. The new secret-env-overrides and secret-env-overrides-base64 properties extend this protection by also redacting values from workflow logs.","date":"2026-04-10T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"bazel","permalink":"/changelog/tags/bazel"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Dan Stowell","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://dstowell.org","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/56944708?v=4","key":"dan","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Improved handling of short-lived secrets in remote execution","date":"2026-04-10T10:00:00.000Z","authors":"dan","tags":["bazel"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"BuildBuddy MCP server","permalink":"/changelog/buildbuddy-mcp-server"},"nextItem":{"title":"Improved GPU and device support for self-hosted executors","permalink":"/changelog/improved-gpu-support"}},"content":"BuildBuddy has supported passing short-lived secrets to remote actions via the `env-overrides` platform property, which redacts values from action cache entries. The new `secret-env-overrides` and `secret-env-overrides-base64` properties extend this protection by also **redacting values from workflow logs**.\\n\\nPass secrets via remote exec headers so they\'re injected at invocation time without affecting the action hash:\\n\\n```bash\\nbazel build //my:target \\\\\\n  --remote_exec_header=x-buildbuddy-platform.secret-env-overrides=API_KEY=sk-abc123,OTHER_KEY=val\\n```\\n\\nFor values containing commas or special characters, base64-encode each `KEY=VALUE` pair:\\n\\n```bash\\nbazel build //my:target \\\\\\n  --remote_exec_header=x-buildbuddy-platform.secret-env-overrides-base64=$(echo -n \'CREDS={\\"token\\": \\"abc\\"}\' | base64)\\n```\\n\\nSee the [Secrets docs](https://www.buildbuddy.io/docs/secrets) and [RBE platform properties reference](https://www.buildbuddy.io/docs/rbe-platforms) for more details."},{"id":"/improved-gpu-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/improved-gpu-support","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/improved-gpu-support.md","source":"@site/changelog/improved-gpu-support.md","title":"Improved GPU and device support for self-hosted executors","description":"GPU support for self-hosted Linux executors is now easier to set up.","date":"2026-03-31T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Brandon Duffany","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/brandon-duffany-39b7217a","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2414826?v=4","key":"brandon","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Improved GPU and device support for self-hosted executors","date":"2026-03-31T10:00:00.000Z","authors":"brandon"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Improved handling of short-lived secrets in remote execution","permalink":"/changelog/secret-env-overrides"},"nextItem":{"title":"Changelog","permalink":"/changelog/changelog"}},"content":"GPU support for self-hosted Linux executors is now easier to set up.\\n\\nBuildBuddy\'s executor image now ships with GPU supporting tools\\n(`nvidia-cdi-hook`), and the executor now supports configuring CDI devices\\nso executors can pass through vendor-provided GPU device configuration to\\nchild containers.\\n\\nSee the new setup docs for details:\\n[GPU support for self-hosted executors](https://buildbuddy.io/docs/config-rbe#gpu-support)."},{"id":"/changelog","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/changelog","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/changelog.md","source":"@site/changelog/changelog.md","title":"Changelog","description":"We\'re excited to introduce the BuildBuddy Changelog!","date":"2026-03-09T12:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Maggie Lou","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/maggie-lou-4a3bb110a/","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13951661","key":"maggie","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Changelog","date":"2026-03-09:12:00:00","authors":"maggie"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Improved GPU and device support for self-hosted executors","permalink":"/changelog/improved-gpu-support"},"nextItem":{"title":"Dark mode","permalink":"/changelog/dark-mode"}},"content":"We\'re excited to introduce the BuildBuddy Changelog!\\n\\nWe\'re a team of builders, but we historically haven\'t always made noise about the features we\'ve built. This changelog is where we\'ll highlight feature launches and meaningful infrastructure improvements.\\n\\nTo get started, we\'re sharing some high-impact features from the past few years that teams may have missed."},{"id":"/dark-mode","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/dark-mode","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/dark-mode.md","source":"@site/changelog/dark-mode.md","title":"Dark mode","description":"We\'re excited to announce dark mode for our UI.","date":"2026-03-09T11:30:00.000Z","tags":[],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Tyler French","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tylerdfrench/","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/66684063?v=4","key":"tyler-french","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Dark mode","date":"2026-03-09T11:30:00.000Z","authors":"tyler-french"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Changelog","permalink":"/changelog/changelog"},"nextItem":{"title":"bb explain: understand why your build re-ran actions","permalink":"/changelog/bb-explain"}},"content":"We\'re excited to announce dark mode for our UI.\\n\\n<video autoPlay loop muted controls playsInline width=\\"100%\\">\\n  <source src=\\"/img/changelog/dark-mode.mp4\\" type=\\"video/mp4\\" />\\n  Your browser does not support the video tag.\\n</video>\\n\\nTo enable, go to **Settings** then **Preferences** under Personal Settings."},{"id":"/bb-explain","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/bb-explain","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/bb-explain.md","source":"@site/changelog/bb-explain.md","title":"bb explain: understand why your build re-ran actions","description":"bb explain shows a structural diff of two compact execution logs. It helps answer the common questions: \\"Why did Bazel re-execute that action?\\" and \\"What changed between these builds?\\"","date":"2026-03-09T11:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"bazel","permalink":"/changelog/tags/bazel"},{"inline":true,"label":"debugging","permalink":"/changelog/tags/debugging"},{"inline":true,"label":"featured","permalink":"/changelog/tags/featured"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Fabian Meumertzheim","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/fhenneke","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4312191?v=4","key":"fabian","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"bb explain: understand why your build re-ran actions","date":"2026-03-09T11:00:00.000Z","authors":"fabian","tags":["bazel","debugging","featured"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Dark mode","permalink":"/changelog/dark-mode"},"nextItem":{"title":"Drilldowns: find similarities between slow or failing builds","permalink":"/changelog/drilldowns"}},"content":"`bb explain` shows a structural diff of two compact execution logs. It helps answer the common questions: \\"Why did Bazel re-execute that action?\\" and \\"What changed between these builds?\\"\\n\\n![bb explain](../static/img/changelog/bb-explain.webp)\\n\\nIt can highlight non-hermetic outputs and differences in inputs, environment variables, and arguments.\\n\\nIt works with your last two builds automatically, or you can point it at any invocation IDs:\\n\\n```\\nbb explain\\nbb explain --old <OLD_INVOCATION_ID> --new <NEW_INVOCATION_ID>\\n```\\n\\nYou can download the `bb` CLI [here](https://www.buildbuddy.io/cli/).\\nMore details in [Fabian\'s BazelCon talk](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jsIzSkaUcx8)."},{"id":"/drilldowns","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/drilldowns","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/drilldowns.md","source":"@site/changelog/drilldowns.md","title":"Drilldowns: find similarities between slow or failing builds","description":"The drilldown view displays heatmaps of build and execution metrics over time. It can help isolate why a subset of builds is slower or failing more often.","date":"2026-03-09T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"debugging","permalink":"/changelog/tags/debugging"},{"inline":true,"label":"featured","permalink":"/changelog/tags/featured"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Jim Hollenbach","title":"Engineer @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/jim-hollenbach-5a49659/","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10570856?v=4","key":"jim","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Drilldowns: find similarities between slow or failing builds","date":"2026-03-09T10:00:00.000Z","authors":"jim","tags":["debugging","featured"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"bb explain: understand why your build re-ran actions","permalink":"/changelog/bb-explain"},"nextItem":{"title":"Compare invocations: compare two builds side-by-side","permalink":"/changelog/compare-invocations"}},"content":"The drilldown view displays heatmaps of build and execution metrics over time. It can help isolate why a subset of builds is slower or failing more often.\\n\\n![](../static/img/changelog/trends-heatmap.webp)\\n\\nYou can select a region of outliers on the heatmap, and Drilldowns will compare that selection against the baseline across dimensions like branch, pattern, and tag.\\n\\nThis makes it easier to spot common characteristics of problematic builds.\\n\\nAvailable on the sidebar under **Drilldowns**."},{"id":"/compare-invocations","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/compare-invocations","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/compare-invocations.md","source":"@site/changelog/compare-invocations.md","title":"Compare invocations: compare two builds side-by-side","description":"The compare invocations view allows you to diff two invocations side-by-side.","date":"2026-03-09T09:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"bazel","permalink":"/changelog/tags/bazel"},{"inline":true,"label":"debugging","permalink":"/changelog/tags/debugging"},{"inline":true,"label":"featured","permalink":"/changelog/tags/featured"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Siggi Simonarson","title":"Co-founder @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/siggisim/","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1704556?v=4","key":"siggi","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Compare invocations: compare two builds side-by-side","date":"2026-03-09T09:00:00.000Z","authors":"siggi","tags":["bazel","debugging","featured"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Drilldowns: find similarities between slow or failing builds","permalink":"/changelog/drilldowns"},"nextItem":{"title":"Compare actions: compare two actions side-by-side","permalink":"/changelog/compare-actions"}},"content":"The compare invocations view allows you to diff two invocations side-by-side.\\n\\n![](../static/img/changelog/compare-invocations.webp)\\n\\nIt can help debug why two builds produced different results by showing exactly what changed: different flags, startup options, cache/remote execution settings, status, and more.\\n\\nTo compare invocations:\\n\\n1. From one invocation link, select **Compare -> Select for comparison** in the top right corner.\\n2. From another invocation link, select **Compare -> Compare with selected**.\\n3. For even more details on differences between the two invocations, click the **Run bb explain** button on the compare invocations page."},{"id":"/compare-actions","metadata":{"permalink":"/changelog/compare-actions","editUrl":"https://github.com/buildbuddy-io/buildbuddy/edit/master/website/changelog/changelog/compare-actions.md","source":"@site/changelog/compare-actions.md","title":"Compare actions: compare two actions side-by-side","description":"The compare actions view allows you to diff two actions side-by-side.","date":"2026-03-09T08:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"bazel","permalink":"/changelog/tags/bazel"},{"inline":true,"label":"debugging","permalink":"/changelog/tags/debugging"},{"inline":true,"label":"featured","permalink":"/changelog/tags/featured"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Siggi Simonarson","title":"Co-founder @ BuildBuddy","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/siggisim/","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1704556?v=4","key":"siggi","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Compare actions: compare two actions side-by-side","date":"2026-03-09T08:00:00.000Z","authors":"siggi","tags":["bazel","debugging","featured"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Compare invocations: compare two builds side-by-side","permalink":"/changelog/compare-invocations"}},"content":"The compare actions view allows you to diff two actions side-by-side.\\n\\n![](../static/img/changelog/compare-actions.webp)\\n\\nThis can help pinpoint why two seemingly similar actions produced different results or didn\'t result in a cache hit.\\n\\nTo compare actions:\\n\\n1. From an invocation link, you can find the desired action either in the `Cache` or `Remote Execution` tabs.\\n1. Click through to the Action Details view.\\n1. Click **Compare -> Select for comparison** in the top right corner.\\n1. Find the other action you want to compare it against.\\n1. Click **Compare -> Compare with selected** in the top right corner of the second action."}]}}')}}]);